Every Linux command returns an exit status code:
0 → Success ✅
1–255 → Error ❌

Example 1 – Success vs failure
ls /etc/passwd
echo $?   # should be 0
ls /not/exist
echo $?   # should be non-zero (like 2)


Example 2 – Error handling in a script
#!/bin/bash
cp /etc/passwd /tmp/
if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then
  echo "Copy successful"
else
  echo "Copy failed"
  exit 1
fi
